HEADWORD: Tawny
<hw>Taw"ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Tawnier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Tawniest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[F. <ets>tann⟦eacute⟧</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>tanner</ets> to tan. See <er>Tan</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos> &
<pos>n.</pos> Cf. <er>Tenn⟦eacute⟧</er>.]</ety> <def>Of a dull yellowish
brown color, like things tanned, or persons who are sunburnt; <as>as,
<ex>tawny</ex> Moor or Spaniard; the <ex>tawny</ex> lion</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A leopard's <xex>tawny</xex> and spotted hide.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
